---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="The Reset | Well-Vie">
	<main>
		<section class="hero slide">
			<span class="hero-label">Path 1</span>
			<h1>The Reset</h1>
			<p class="subtitle">
				For women seeking deeper connection, nervous system support, breathwork,
				and intentional community.
			</p>
			<p>
				A 3 week experience designed to help women slow down, reflect,
				reconnect to themselves, and experience breathwork, nervous system
				support, community, and honest conversation.
			</p>
			<a href="#what-to-expect" class="btn">Begin Your Journey</a>
		</section>

		<hr class="divider" />

		<span id="what-to-expect" class="section-anchor" aria-hidden="true"></span>
		<section class="expect slide">
			<h2>What to Expect</h2>
			<div class="week-list">
				<article class="week-card">
					<h3>Week One</h3>
					<h4>Connect &amp; Set Intentions</h4>
					<p>
						Our first week is designed to help you slow down and reconnect.
					</p>
					<p>
						Together, we'll begin with a 90-minute LIVE community call where
						you'll meet the women inside your group, share introductions, and
						set intentions for the journey ahead. We'll move through a guided
						breathwork session and explore simple nervous system practices to
						support you throughout the week.
					</p>
					<p>
						You'll also receive journal prompts and reflection exercises to help
						you integrate the experience and reconnect with yourself in everyday
						life.
					</p>
					<p class="week-emphasis">
						<strong>
							This week is about building a foundation and creating space for
							what comes next.
						</strong>
					</p>
				</article>

				<article class="week-card">
					<h3>Week Two</h3>
					<h4>Deepen &amp; Receive Support</h4>
					<p>Our second week is designed to help you go deeper.</p>
					<p>
						Together, we'll gather for a 90-minute LIVE session beginning with a
						guided breathwork and nervous system reset. From there, we'll move
						into meaningful conversation centered around what you're currently
						navigating and wanting support with.
					</p>
					<p>
						You'll learn practical somatic tools to bring into everyday life,
						have space to ask questions, and connect with other women walking
						through similar seasons.
					</p>
					<p class="week-emphasis">
						<strong>
							This week is about feeling seen, supported, and remembering that
							you don't have to carry everything alone.
						</strong>
					</p>
				</article>

				<article class="week-card">
					<h3>Week Three</h3>
					<h4>Reconnect &amp; Reset</h4>
					<p>
						Our final week is designed to help you integrate and move forward
						with intention.
					</p>
					<p>
						We'll come together for a 90-minute LIVE closing session,
						reconnecting through guided breathwork, reflection, and integration.
						This is an opportunity to celebrate your growth, revisit the
						intentions you set at the beginning of the experience, and create
						space for what comes next.
					</p>
					<p>
						You'll leave with practices and journal prompts to continue
						supporting yourself long after the three weeks have ended.
					</p>
					<p>
						This week is about honoring how far you've come and moving forward
						with greater clarity, connection, and self-awareness.
					</p>
				</article>

				<article class="program-included">
					<h3>Included Throughout</h3>
					<ul class="included-throughout-list">
						<li>Three LIVE 90-minute sessions</li>
						<li>Guided breathwork journeys</li>
						<li>Nervous system support and somatic practices</li>
						<li>Journal prompts and reflection exercises</li>
						<li>Community and connection</li>
						<li>Replay access available if life gets in the way</li>
						<li>An intimate group setting (limited to 15 women)</li>
					</ul>
				</article>

				<article class="bonus-card">
					<p class="section-label">Bonus Feature</p>
					<h3>Private WhatsApp Community</h3>
					<p>
						Throughout the three weeks, you'll have access to a private
						WhatsApp group with the women inside your cohort. This space is
						open for questions, reflections, celebrations, and honest
						conversations as you move through the experience together.
					</p>
					<p>
						Think of it as an extension of our calls&mdash;a place to feel
						supported, stay connected, and remember that you don't have to
						navigate this journey alone.
					</p>
					<p class="week-emphasis">
						<strong>
							Some of the most meaningful moments happen between the calls.
						</strong>
					</p>
				</article>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="details slide">
			<div class="details-inner">
				<h2>Details</h2>
				<div class="details-grid">
					<div class="detail-item">
						<dt>Start Date</dt>
						<dd>September 15, 2026</dd>
					</div>
					<div class="detail-item">
						<dt>Investment</dt>
						<dd>USD $333</dd>
					</div>
				</div>
				<p>Optional payment plan available.</p>
				<p class="limited">
					Spots are intentionally limited to 15 women to preserve the intimacy
					and intentionality of the experience.
				</p>
				<a href="/reset/apply/" class="btn">Apply</a>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="closing slide">
			<h2>What Comes After?</h2>
			<p>
				Women who complete Path I will receive priority access to Path II &
				Path III, retreats, workshops, in-person gatherings and future Well-Vie
				experiences.
			</p>
			<a href="/ecosystem/#path-ii-waitlist" class="btn">Join the Waitlist</a>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 2rem;
		padding-top: var(--section-gap);
		padding-bottom: var(--section-gap);
		max-width: 900px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: var(--section-gap);
	}

	/* Hero */
	.hero {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		gap: var(--small-gap);
		padding-block: var(--element-gap);
	}

	.hero-label {
		font-family: var(--gt-walsheim);
		font-size: var(--paragraph);
		letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--text-color);
	}

	.hero h1 {
		font-size: var(--subheading);
		color: var(--fg-color);
		margin-top: 0.25rem;
	}

	.hero .subtitle {
		font-family: var(--roslindale);
		font-size: var(--heading-paragraph);
		color: var(--fg-color);
		max-width: 600px;
		margin-top: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.hero > p:not(.subtitle) {
		max-width: 580px;
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	.hero .btn {
		margin-top: var(--element-gap);
	}

	/* Dividers */
	.divider {
		width: 60px;
		border: none;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--fg-light-color);
		margin: 0;
	}

	.section-anchor {
		display: block;
		scroll-margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	/* What to Expect */
	.expect {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		gap: var(--element-gap);
		width: 100%;
	}

	.week-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--element-gap);
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
	}

	.week-card {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding-bottom: var(--element-gap);
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--fg-light-color);
	}

	.week-card:last-child {
		padding-bottom: 0;
		border-bottom: none;
	}

	.week-card h3 {
		color: var(--fg-color);
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4rem);
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.week-card h4 {
		font-family: var(--roslindale);
		font-size: var(--heading-paragraph);
		color: var(--fg-color);
		font-weight: normal;
	}

	.week-card p {
		max-width: 620px;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.week-emphasis {
		margin-top: 0.5rem;
	}

	.program-included,
	.bonus-card {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding-top: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.program-included h3,
	.bonus-card h3 {
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 4rem);
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.included-throughout-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		list-style: none;
		color: var(--text-color);
		font-size: var(--paragraph);
	}

	.included-throughout-list li {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 0.75rem;
	}

	.included-throughout-list li::before {
		content: "";
		display: inline-block;
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background-color: var(--fg-light-color);
		flex-shrink: 0;
	}

	.section-label {
		font-family: var(--gt-walsheim);
		font-size: 1rem;
		letter-spacing: 0.15em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--text-color);
	}

	.bonus-card p:not(.section-label) {
		max-width: 620px;
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	/* Details band */
	.details {
		width: calc(100% + 4rem);
		margin-inline: -2rem;
		background-color: var(--fg-color);
		border-radius: var(--border-radius);
		padding: var(--section-gap) 2rem;
	}

	.details-inner {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		gap: var(--small-gap);
		max-width: 500px;
		margin: 0 auto;
	}

	.details-inner h2 {
		color: var(--bg-color);
		margin-bottom: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.details-grid {
		display: flex;
		gap: var(--horizontal-gap);
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		margin-bottom: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.detail-item {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 0.25rem;
	}

	.detail-item dt {
		font-family: var(--roslindale);
		font-size: var(--heading-paragraph);
		color: var(--bg-color);
	}

	.detail-item dd {
		font-family: var(--gt-walsheim);
		font-size: var(--paragraph);
		color: var(--bg-color);
		margin: 0;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.details-inner p {
		color: var(--bg-color);
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.details-inner .limited {
		font-style: italic;
		margin-top: var(--small-gap);
		opacity: 0.85;
	}

	/* Closing */
	.closing {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		gap: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.closing h2 {
		margin-bottom: var(--small-gap);
	}

	.closing p {
		max-width: 580px;
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	.closing .btn {
		margin-top: var(--element-gap);
	}
</style>
